{"_id":"0her9fqDEQGD0sd0","name":"Fight with the Owlbear","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">The Owlbear</h1>\n<p>Lagraa and her cronies lead Owlbear onto deck just after the evening meal “for a bit of sport” and dare one of the PCs to take him on—bare-knuckle fists or wrestling only, no magic tricks, and the last one conscious wins. To make it interesting, Lagraa tosses down a purse of 100 gp as a wager on Owlbear.</p>\n<p>Owlbear Hartshorn is a large man with meaty fists. He’s a bit simple, and the rest of the crew enjoys having a laugh at the poor fellow’s expense. To try to make friends, Hartshorn has taken to clowning, laughing, and crying out random phrases at the top of his voice, as this seems to make people laugh. Owlbear's shaved skin still shows signs of the tarring and feathering the crew gave him as a cruel joke not so long ago.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Owlbear Hartshorn]{Owlbear Hartshorn}</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Tactics</h3>\n<p>If Shaken, Mr. Lagraa throws owlbear a club to use in the fight. If owlbear takes a wound, he cries and tries to back away, but is pushed back into combat my Mr. Lagraa and her mates.</p>\n<h3>Development</h3>\n<p>If the swab defeats Owlbear, that character gains a +1 bonus to all future social checks to influence anyone on the ship for the remainder of the adventure. If the swab backs away when Owlbear does, he gains an even more valuable boon—Owlbear’s friendship. The towering hulk is not used to being treated with respect and kindness, and becomes helpful in attitude to that swab for the rest of the adventure.</p>\n<p>Mr. Lagraa keeps a close eye on the other swabs, and if anyone attempts to fix the fight with magic, or if the swab fighting Owlbear draws a weapon, the offending character is given six lashes for the transgression. If the swab kills Owlbear, the punishment is a dozen lashes with the cat.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"quick-encounters":{"quickEncounter":"{\"journalEntryId\":\"MMMTZcygBDdHuIMw\",\"extractedActors\":[{\"numActors\":1,\"dataPackName\":\"savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary\",\"actorID\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"name\":\" Krornik Kragshard\",\"savedTokensData\":[],\"generatedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}],\"combinedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}]}],\"hideQE\":true,\"qeVersion\":\"0.8.4\"}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5m4g64zt3jr","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/3. Aboard the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"260fKdr6NlF3cscp","name":"A Night Forgotten","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">A Night Forgotten</h1>\n<p>All the following options revolve around your would-be pirate being in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}, and the circumstances that brought you to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron} tavern.  Your unfortunate night at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron} has you running afoul of a press gang from the pirate ship <em>Storm Reaver</em>. Choose one of the options below for your evening in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}, or come up with something along these similiar lines.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Old friend:</span> You have been searching for the right crew to join for your next adventure. Funds are low and you will need more if you are going to be able to accomplish anything for other Cyrans. A meeting with a contact had been arranged at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron} in Pier's End. The meeting went well,and a few more drinks in celebration followed. A few more drinks, but surely not enough to black out...</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">The Sea Calls:</span> You came to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} in search of finding a new home now that Cyre is gone. Niether @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Sharn]{Sharn}, nor @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.New Cyre]{New Cyre}, or any of the other ghettos can rightfully be called a home. After a few drinks at the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron}, you went down to the docks to take in the view of the sea and the ships at port. The last thing you remember is a blow to the back of your head and the waves ruching up to meet you.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">A hero in cramped quarters:</span>  You were between ships in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}, and after stopping for a drink at a tavern called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron}, you happened upon a damsel in distress in the alleyway outside. Thinking you could help, you didn’t notice the thugs hiding nearby, and they caught you unawares. You’ve been on enough ships to know a press gang by the blow of the sap on the back of your neck. You just hope whatever ship you end up on has a respectable captain.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Wasted plunder:</span>  You found yourself relatively well off when you got your share of your last voyage’s plunder, and decided to spend a few of your hard-won coins at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron}, a popular sailor tavern in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}. Maybe the shine of your new wealth distracted you, however, because you never saw the miscreants who slipped something into your drink, knocking you out cold.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Nothing like a good tavern brawl:</span> The atmosphere of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron} has always been to your liking. Boisterious, lively, folk of the sea, a little bit shady, and you have always loved the cats there. Last night was another lively night. After a few drinks last night, you found yourself uncharacteristically joining into a brawl that started. Though you handled yourself well and just defending your new life long friend's honor. As you staggered around the corner to relieve yourself, you were set upon by a group of rough-looking thugs. They overwhlemed you and knocked you unconscious. At least you hope you did soil your pants.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Arawai's Blessing:</span>  You came to a tavern in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron} in search of your fate or maybe just another ship to join. You’re not sure how many drinks you had, but they quickly went to your head and you passed out on the table before you found your destiny—unless it lay in the bottom of a bottle. Then again, maybe you found your destiny after all...</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Barron Tailspinner:</span>  You went to a tavern called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron} in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} to earn a few coins with your tales of the sea. The patrons seemed pleased with your performance and bought you a few drinks. You had just remembered a tale of an unfortunate sailor who found himself press-ganged on a pirate ship after his drink was drugged when suddenly everything went black.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Cabin Fever:</span> It took you a few months to sail here from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Sharn]{Sharn} aboard the <em>Tiger Princess</em>. That was way too long to be at sea without any stops. You arrived here in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} almost a week ago, and you are finally starting to feel like you have made up for the time lost on the <em>Tiger Princess</em>. One more night at a new spot wouldn't hurt. You heard numerous good rumors about the ale and games at the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and The Baron}, and so it was time to check it out. You promised yourself this night you would only have one drink and have your wits about you to finally remeber what you can learn about what is happening in this city. You don't remember anything after that first drink.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":4},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_sfbrzx24rkb","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Player Character Guide","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"276jgwCRrWKYcf0I","name":"04 Skeleton Crew","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Skeleton Crew</h1>\n<p>At dawn, a few hours after the celebration finally winds down, the ship’s bell sounds, calling all hands on deck. When the crew is assembled, a long line of captured officers and sailors from the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> is brought on deck and paraded before the crew. Prince Rockface addresses the captives first, offering a place on the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew for any who want to throw their lot in with pirates. Several of the Rahadoumi sailors step forward; Master Scourge cuts their bonds, and the sailors take their places among the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew. Prince Rockface then turns to address the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew.</p>\n<aside class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>“All right, you scurvy tars! You’ve done a right good job by me—we’ve got a second ship now, and she’s quite a prize from the looks of her. But I still have only one crew. So here’s the plan—the <em>Storm Reaver</em> will sail on to our planned destination with our new shipmates here, while Mister Lagraa will pick a skeleton crew to sail the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> to Port Krez, where she’ll be worth a pretty penny as salvage.</p>\n<p>“As for these fine fellows here”—Prince Rockface gestures at the remainder of the captured ship’s crew—“some of them will no doubt be worth a hefty ransom from their families back in Breland. And for the rest, if the life of a pirate’s not for them, they can spend the rest of their lives at sea!”</p>\n</aside>\n<p>To make her point, Prince Rockface grabs one of the Brelish sailors and throws her overboard to the accompaniment of cheers and laughter from the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew. As the unfortunate woman sinks beneath the waves, many of the remaining sailors scramble to swear their loyalty to Prince Rockface. The officers are led belowdecks and the crew begins to disperse to their daily tasks.</p>\n<p>As they do, Mister Lagraa and Master Scourge pick out several of the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> original crew, telling them to be aboard the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> within 10 minutes to set sail for Port Krez. The swabs are chosen to join the skeleton crew as well, and Scourge smiles evilly at them as he picks them. The swabs have little time left on the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, but allow them to gather whatever gear or loot they may have acquired, and give them one last chance to purchase supplies from the quartermaster’s store. If any of the swabs have befriended Cut-Throat Grok, she cries as they leave. If she was made helpful, she gives them a gift worth 100 gp from the stores on parting.</p>\n<p>The skeleton crew of the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> includes the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mister Lagraa (now Captain)</li>\n<li>Master Scourage (now First Mate)</li>\n<li>Patch \"Salty\" Kolkrinun</li>\n<li>Krornik \"Fishguts\" Kragshard</li>\n<li>Owlbear Hartshorn</li>\n<li>The rest of the original crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>.</li>\n<li>The swabs</li>\n</ul>\n<p>At this stage, ensure that there at least eight <em>Storm Reaver</em> pirates loyal to Plugg and Scourge (meaning unfriendly or hostile toward the swabs) aboard the <em>Majestic Griffon</em>. If there are not enough loyal pirates, make up the numbers with Brelish sailors who are naturally grateful to Mister Lagraa for sparing them and allowing them to join his crew. Once everyone is aboard with their gear, the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> sets sail.</p>\n<h2>New Ship, Harsher Discipline</h2>\n<p>As the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> sets sail, acting captain Mister Lagraa and her first mate Master Scourge gather the crew together to inform them that although this is a new ship, the rules are the same, though discipline on the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> will be a good deal harsher than on the lackadaisical <em>Storm Reaver</em>— all crimes are now punishable with the cat instead of the whip. All of the crew keep the same jobs they had before on the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, but they will have to work a good deal harder, as the crew is smaller.</p>\n<p><strong>Fatigue: </strong>From now on all checks to avoid @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} on the ship are made at a -2 penalty. Tasks that did not have a Vigor check for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, now require a Vigor check.</p>\n<p>Master Scourge ensures that the swabs continue to have the worst jobs of the crew for the remainder of this journey (you should assign the swabs the worst duties or the duties they most hate every day rather than rolling randomly). As night falls, the sails of the <em>Storm Reaver</em> disappear over the horizon. Mister Lagraa does not believe in crew entertainment or rum rations, and anyone caught above decks after dusk without leave gets six lashes with the cat. At your discretion, gambling might still go on belowdecks, but it is quite likely that Mister Lagraa and Scourge will hear about it and act accordingly.</p>\n<h3>New Destination</h3>\n<p>That night, Mister Lagraa, Scourge, and those pirates loyal to them hold a secret meeting in the captain’s cabin, where they plot to sail the ship not to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Port Krez]{Port Krez}, but to a dry dock in Cliff's End called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Rickety's Squibs]{Rickety's Squibs}, where they can make the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> their own and engage in piracy for themselves. Mister Lagraa and Scourge want only the most loyal crew with them, however, and plan to do away with the swabs and their friends as soon as Rickety’s Squibs is in sight. </p>\n<p>Friendly crew members begin whispering their concerns to the swabs by the second day of the voyage. If the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> is sailing back to Port Krez, what is to become of the group of press-ganged crew? Rumors begin to spread among the friendly crew members that Mister Lagraa might decide to claim the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> for himself and establish himself as a pirate captain in his own right. These rumors become more certain when a friendly cremember deduces (if the swabs haven’t already) that the ship has changed course and is heading west past @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Tidewater Rock]{Tidewater Rock} and into Cliff's End. If the swabs have not considered staging a mutiny themselves, friendly crewmembers begin making that suggestion for them, but only when the time is right. </p>\n<p>During the evening, Kragshard suggests to the swabs that he knows where the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> might be heading—to a seedy, isolated dry dock in Cliff's End called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Rickety's Squibs]{Rickety's Squibs}. For a price, old Rickety Hake completely refits ships into “squibs,” providing new identities by changing ships’ lines, silhouettes, and general appearance to be unrecognizable to their former owners or anyone else familiar with them.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"quick-encounters":{"quickEncounter":"{\"journalEntryId\":\"MMMTZcygBDdHuIMw\",\"extractedActors\":[{\"numActors\":1,\"dataPackName\":\"savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary\",\"actorID\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"name\":\" Krornik Kragshard\",\"savedTokensData\":[],\"generatedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}],\"combinedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}]}],\"hideQE\":true,\"qeVersion\":\"0.8.4\"}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0gxlbqom8dl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/1. Mourners of Lhazaar Plot Point","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"3hooq1e9mFdU5dNB","name":"Officer's Hall and Armory","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Officer's Mess and Armory</h1>\n<p>This tiny chamber is crammed with chests and neatly ordered weapon racks. The armory is secured with a good lock (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check (–2)) and trapped with a harpoon trap at each door.</p>\n<p>Among all the crates and weapons racks there are a couple tables here. The officers gather here in the evening to have thier  meal seperate from the crew.</p>\n<p>The weapon racks hold 20 clubs, 12 heavy crossbows, 20 cutlasses , 50 javelins, 12 shortspears, and 20 grappling hooks each attached to 50 feet of rope.</p>\n<p>Two chests contain 500 heavy crossbow bolts each, while three other chests each hold 12 flasks of alchemist’s fire. Four other chests each contain a breastplate, chain shirt, and buckler.</p>\n<p>The ship’s master gunner, @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Riaris Krine]{Riaris Krine}, is meticulous in her job and quickly spots any obvious thefts, in which case an immediate search of the crew’s lockers is made. Anyone found in possession of stolen items from the armory is given six lashes with the cat for a first offense, or is keelhauled for a second offense.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Krornik Kragshard]{Krornik Kragshard} and @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Cut-Throat Grok]{Cut-Throat Grok} sleep here in the evenings.</p>\n<h2 class=\"trap\">Harpoon Trap</h2>\n<p><strong>Type:</strong> Mechanical; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} Check:</strong> Yes, at –1; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} Check:</strong> Yes, at –1</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger:</strong> If the door handle is not used in a specific way when the door is opened a harpoon will shoot at the door.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> The pirate that triggers the trap must make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} roll to dive clear or be struck by the harpoon ([[/r d8x+d6x=]] damage).</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_e26boiu8etj","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"50t3vOrETGvU1bQL","name":"Mess Hall","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Mess Hall</h1>\n<p>The Mess Hall hasa storage room immediately to the left that holds more equipment for Grok as outlined in the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Quartermasters Store]{Quartermasters Store}.</p>\n<p>The rest of the mess hall contains three tables, number crates and barrels with supplies of food stuff. There are score of chickens and three goats that freely wander this chamber. The goats are meant to be caged but have a distressing tendency to escape their bonds. </p>\n<p>Evening meals are taken here and during the evening there is often gambling or other entertainments to be had here.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_e26boiu8etj","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"565axwczkrQNYLJU","name":"05 New Ship, Stricter Rules","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">New Ship</h1>\n<p>At dawn, a few hours after the celebration finally winds down, the ship’s bell sounds, calling all hands on deck. When the crew is assembled, a long line of captured officers and sailors from the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> is brought on deck and paraded before the crew. Prince Rockface addresses the captives first, offering a place on the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew for any who want to throw their lot in with pirates. Several of the Rahadoumi sailors step forward; Master Scourge cuts their bonds, and the sailors take their places among the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew. Prince Rockface then turns to address the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew.</p>\n<aside class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>“All right, you scurvy tars! You’ve done a right good job by me—we’ve got a second ship now, and she’s quite a prize from the looks of her. But I still have only one crew. So here’s the plan—the <em>Storm Reaver</em> will sail on to our planned destination with our new shipmates here, while Mister Lagraa will pick a skeleton crew to sail the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> to Port Krez, where she’ll be worth a pretty penny as salvage.</p>\n<p>“As for these fine fellows here”—Prince Rockface gestures at the remainder of the captured ship’s crew—“some of them will no doubt be worth a hefty ransom from their families back in Breland. And for the rest, if the life of a pirate’s not for them, they can spend the rest of their lives at sea!”</p>\n</aside>\n<p>To make her point, Prince Rockface grabs one of the Brelish sailors and throws her overboard to the accompaniment of cheers and laughter from the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew. As the unfortunate woman sinks beneath the waves, many of the remaining sailors scramble to swear their loyalty to Prince Rockface. The officers are led belowdecks and the crew begins to disperse to their daily tasks.</p>\n<p>As they do, Mister Lagraa and Master Scourge pick out several of the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> original crew, telling them to be aboard the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> within 10 minutes to set sail for Port Krez. The swabs are chosen to join the skeleton crew as well, and Scourge smiles evilly at them as he picks them. The swabs have little time left on the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, but allow them to gather whatever gear or loot they may have acquired, and give them one last chance to purchase supplies from the quartermaster’s store. If any of the swabs have befriended Cut-Throat Grok, she cries as they leave. If she was made helpful, she gives them a gift worth 100 gp from the stores on parting.</p>\n<p>The skeleton crew of the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> includes the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mister Lagraa (now Captain)</li>\n<li>Master Scourage (now First Mate)</li>\n<li>Patch \"Salty\" Kolkrinun</li>\n<li>Krornik \"Fishguts\" Kragshard</li>\n<li>Owlbear Hartshorn</li>\n<li>The rest of the original crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>.</li>\n<li>The swabs</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Stricter Rules</h2>\n<p>Discipline aboard the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> will be a good deal harsher. All crimes are now punishable by the cat instead of the whip. Everyone will have to work harder than they did before. Any job not requiring a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} check now does. Any job having a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} now has an additional –1 to it's check. The swabs will have the worst jobs aboard the new ship. Miser Lagraa does not believe in entertainment nor @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Grog Ration]{grog ration}.</p>\n<h2>New Destination and Another Storm</h2>\n<p>Within a day or so the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> will clearly start heading south west instead of west. As it nears @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Tidewater Rock]{Tidewater Rock} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Traglorn Island]{Traglorn Island} a storm will hit the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> in the early hours of the morning. The <em>Majestic Griffon</em> is blown way off course and all hands are call to work on the deck. All hands are required to work in the rigging, given random @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Rigging Tasks}]{Rigging Tasks}. </p>\n<p>As the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> struggles off course, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check at –2 for swabs to see the dark shapes loom out of the sea all around the ship. Small islets and coral reefs that dot this area. The storm is fierce being the equivelant of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dark illumination}.</p>\n<p>At this point a few grindylows will board the ship and make off with a couple of tasty sailors, Sandara Quinn among them. Emboldened by their success more grindylows attack the beleaguered ship for more food. They flee when half or more of them have been slain.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Grindylow]{Grindylow} (6)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Shipwrecked</h2>\n<p>As the storm begins to abate, the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> hits the coral reefs surrounding @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Bonewreck Isle]{Bonewreck Isle} and runs aground. As the sun rises and the tide goes out, the members of the crew slowly come to terms with their predicament. The <em>Majestic Griffon</em> is holed in the main hold. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} check is enough to surmise that although the ship is not in immediate danger of sinking, she’ll eventually sink unless repairs are made. Mister Lagraa immediately instructs several of the crew to begin dismantling the ship’s deck to repair the vessel.</p>\n<p>Early in the morning, Mister Lagraa calls the roll of the crew, and two of the ship’s sailors are discovered to be missing. One of the missing crew members is Sandara Quinn; the other should be chosen randomly from among those pirates most friendly to the swabs. Mister Lagraa is dismissive of the two pirates’ fate.</p>\n<p>At the same time, the crew discovers that the ship’s water barrel burst when the vessel ran aground and is now empty. Mister Lagraa orders the swabs to take one of the ship’s cutters and a couple of empty barrels and find fresh water and supplies on the nearby island. She tells the swabs that the ship will depart when repairs are done, whether they are back or not.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"quick-encounters":{"quickEncounter":"{\"journalEntryId\":\"MMMTZcygBDdHuIMw\",\"extractedActors\":[{\"numActors\":1,\"dataPackName\":\"savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary\",\"actorID\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"name\":\" Krornik Kragshard\",\"savedTokensData\":[],\"generatedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}],\"combinedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}]}],\"hideQE\":true,\"qeVersion\":\"0.8.4\"}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_0gxlbqom8dl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/1. Mourners of Lhazaar Plot Point","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"6FlQO0u8yXnaCI2G","name":"A Toast to Death","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">A Toast to Death</h1>\n<p>Arni Amill offers to sell the group three units worth of wine for just $100 per unit on the condition the wine is only sold in a pirate town. He claims it is a peace offering to pirate crews to leave Wrasseton alone—in fact he has a far more sinister plan.</p>\n<p>Following the death of his family Arni began plotting his revenge. The wine has been doctored with a slow-acting but deadly poison. The once mild-mannered Arni is planning an act of genocide. Each mug of wine requires the drinker to make a Vigor roll. Failure results in death within 2d6 hours.</p>\n<p>The group can find a buyer on a successful Streetwise roll. A Persuasion roll is required to determine the price. On a success the buyer offers $300 per unit increasing by $100 for each raise.</p>\n<p>Within a matter of days several hundred pirates die from the deadly brew. Sadly for the characters, the pirates blame them and come looking for the poisoners. Several pirate captains collectively place a bounty of 1,000 pieces of eight on each character’s head.</p>\n<p>On any encounter with pirates—on land or at sea—draw an additional card. If the card is black the pirates have heard of the poisoning and seek revenge on the group.</p>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_53dtyb3i8lp","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/2. Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"74EZcqJ5lT4XnZaH","name":"Wreck of the Carcanus","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Wreck of the Carcanus</h1>\n<p>The Carcanus limped into the Teeth after the kraken’s epic battle with the Sea Hags. The crew did not make it and Tressa has since taken its usable goods, but the magical sails remain intact.</p>\n<p>The Carcanus lies in 60’ of water—just deep enough to require either aquatic characters or magic of some sort. Cutting the sails free takes at least 15 minutes. They can then be hoisted aboard by the crew and put in place in 2d6 hours.</p>\n<p> Sharks (200): 2d6 man-eaters and two great whites are in the area.</p>\n<p> Booty: Loot (the ship has been mostly looted), Sharkskin Sails.</p>\n<p>Sharkskin Sails: Made from the hide of the great ugak Walking God, Jinka-Tahn, these slick gray sails increase the Travel Speed of any vessel mounting them by one.</p>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_53dtyb3i8lp","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/2. Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"8579PWn4dLL6v9kV","name":"Something in the Bilges","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Something in the Bilges</h1>\n<p>The PCs should not be assigned duty in the bilges today. If such work is indicated, roll again to find new tasks for the PCs.</p>\n<p>At about mid-morning on the fourth day, Giffer Tibbs rushes onto deck. A successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check can see his ashen face as well as overhear what he reports to Mr. Lagraa. Giffer was below on rat-catching duty when something big swam out of the bilge water and bit him. Lagraa immediately looks for volunteers to investigate, and selects all of the new pirates (including the cook’s mate), telling them to get down to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Bilges]{bilges} and not bother coming out until whatever is down there is dead.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Rat, Dire]{Dire Rats} (6)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Tactics</h3>\n<p>Six dire rats have gnawed their way out of a dodgy consignment of barley the captain picked up in Regalport on the cheap, and have taken up residence in the brackish water in the bilges. Today the weather is so blistering that the bilges are considered @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heat]{very hot}. A rat is found every [[/r (1d6)*(1d8+4)]] minutes while down in the bilges. Swabs must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (–4) or be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Surprise]{surprised} when the rats strike from the water.</p>\n<h3>Treasure</h3>\n<p>Searching of the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Bilges]{bilges} could reward the swabs with the items that are forgotten down there.</p>\n<h2 class=\"aftermath\">Aftermath</h2>\n<p>If the swabs spend more than 4 hours in the bilges, Mr. Lagraa sends one of the pirates down to tell them if they can’t deal with one tiny creature in half an hour, they each get three lashes. If the swabs fail to kill all of the rats, they’re likely to bite someone else, an event that earns the swabs three lashes each. In that case, the following day Mr. Lagraa automatically assigns only one swab (to prevent time wasting) to the bilges again.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"quick-encounters":{"quickEncounter":"{\"journalEntryId\":\"MMMTZcygBDdHuIMw\",\"extractedActors\":[{\"numActors\":1,\"dataPackName\":\"savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary\",\"actorID\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"name\":\" Krornik Kragshard\",\"savedTokensData\":[],\"generatedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}],\"combinedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}]}],\"hideQE\":true,\"qeVersion\":\"0.8.4\"}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5m4g64zt3jr","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/3. Aboard the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"9vDtVs0UJSbZ7wIz","name":"Session 0","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Session 0</h1>\n<h2>Setting Rules for Character Creation</h2>\n<p>These are the following setting rules we will use. I am open to using others if you want.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Born A Hero]{Born A Hero}:</strong> Player characters ignore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} requirements for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Character Creation Summary]{character creation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Born from War]{Born from War}:</strong> Player characters start with one free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Class}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Background} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Professional Edge}. This edge must be tied to the story of your characters experiences during her life in the Last War during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Character Creation Summary]{character creation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Creative Combat]{Creative Combat}:</strong> A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} allows the character to roll on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Creative Combat]{special table} that grants additional effects.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dynamic Backlash]{Dynamic Backlash}:</strong> A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane} skill roll forces the player to roll on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dynamic Backlash]{special table} with various chaotic results.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fanatics]{Fanatics}:</strong> Enemy thugs take the damage for their masters.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory and Infamy}:</strong> Glory or Infamy track the reputation of the Player Characters. As it increases they are awarded with benefits from those that respect the reputation of the character.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.More Skill Points]{More Skill Points}:</strong> Player characters in advanced or specialized settings start with 15 skill points.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unarmored Hero]{Unarmored Hero}:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} without armor add +2 to their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Character and Campaign Backstory</h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Pirates of Cyre Characters]{Pirates of Cyre Characters}:</strong> Review this journal entry for information and details on the intent of campaign and the broader place your character some come from to fit int this campaign.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Campaign Summary]{Campaign Summary}:</strong> Review this journal entry for a brief overview of the arc of the campaign and how it will have started for your character.</p>\n<h2>Character Creation</h2>\n<p><strong>Character Creation: </strong>You will find links to all necessary hindrances, skills, edges, gear and other things within Foundry through the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Character Creation Summary]{Character Creation Summary} page.</p>\n<p><strong>World Building: </strong>Read and answer the questions @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Pirates of Cyre World Development]{Pirates of Cyre World Development} particularly for World Building. Provide your answers to the Dungeon Master.</p>\n<p><strong>Cyran Heritage: </strong>Considering you are from Cyre, look at the document on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Cyran Characters]{Cyran Characters}. Take the time to answer some of the questions posted there to build out your drive for the campaign and how your Cyran heritage manifests in your character.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"journalentry","_viewcount":7},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_sfbrzx24rkb","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Player Character Guide","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"9vVuPgzUZDmBtiAw","name":"Weapons Deck","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Weapons Deck</h1>\n<p>The weapons deck is also the place that the crew sleeps at night. Down here are 10 ballistas, 5 per side. In the bow there is a siege staff mounted to ship that are maintained and used by <span style=\"color:#3598db\">@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Grovus Stormbread]{Grovus Stormbread}</span> and <span style=\"color:#3598db\">@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Hakrilli Quarne]{Hakrilli Quarne}</span>. Anyone caught tampering with the siege staff  gets 6 lashes during Bloody Hour.</p>\n<p>There is a large hole to move cargo to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Cargo Hold]{Cargo Hold}. To the fore of it there are 12 barrels of oil containing 20 gallons of oil each. To the aft are 12 barrels of freshwater holding 50 gallons each for the crew.</p>\n<p>Towards the bow there are two ladders port and starboard. The ladders up lead to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Map Room]{Map Room}. It is common knowledge that the hatches above are trapped. The ladders that go down lead to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Cargo Hold]{Cargo Hold}. Center aft there is a staircase up to the hall near the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Galley]{Galley} and @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Quartermasters Store]{Quartermasters Store}, while there is a ladder down to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers Quarters]{Officers Quarters}. To the very aft are two doors that lead to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officer's Hall and Armory]{Officer's Hall and Armory}.</p>\n<h3>Crew Lockers</h3>\n<p>There are numerous lockers down here, one for each of the crew. Each locker can be picked with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check. Each locker contains [[/r 10d10]] in sovereigns and [[/r 1d10]] in galifars. Additionally they contain [[/r 1d3]] items from the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Crew Lockers]{Crew Lockers} table. The crew generally refers to this cache as their duffle.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_e26boiu8etj","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"AviffuRHzsXotGr5","name":"Hijack the Immortal","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Hijack the Immortal</h1>\n<p>The Immortal, the British East Indiaman reported captured in the Savage Tale Trade War, lies in port at New Madrid. Frederico Pires and the Spanish Guild are refitting her for their own use and are wary of agents for the British East India Company attempting to steal her back.</p>\n<p>If the characters are in Baltimus, they might be approached by the Company to lead a hijacking crew. They’re looking for independent agents to do the dirty work so that they can deny the action should they be caught. If the heroes can sail the frigate back to Baltimus, they’ll be rewarded 20,000 pieces of eight.</p>\n<p>Guards (184): Five guards sit on the docks, five more are on the upper deck. Use City Watch statistics for the guards (page 184).</p>\n<h2>Working the Other Side</h2>\n<p>If the group are well-known to the Spanish Guild, they might be hired on as “additional security” instead. The job pays $50 per man per night, a healthy fee for this kind of work. The British East India Company hires a raiding party in this case as well. Roll a d6 each night the heroes are on guard duty. On a 6, the raiders strike.</p>\n<p>Ten guards (use City Watch statistics, page 184)) are on duty with the heroes. They’re stationed as above unless the “consultants” say otherwise.</p>\n<p> Raiders (5): A party of five daring adventurers strike. Create these individuals on your own just like player characters equivalent in Rank to your own crew.</p>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_53dtyb3i8lp","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/2. Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"BIeSA05DkU7BT5N1","name":"Sandara Quinn","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Life is never easy, and Sandara Quinn’s life has been typical of that truism. The daughter of a poor fisherman and a seamstress, Sandara was raised in Hell Harbor. Her overworked parents had little time to spend with their daughter, and Sandara grew up on the port’s hard streets, where she quickly learned to look after herself. She worked on the docks when she could, carrying out what jobs she could get, and soon developed a keen eye for trouble and a reputation for standing up for herself. She began frequenting the bars and taverns of Hell Harbor by the age of 9 and was learning the ropes of sailing by the age of 12.</p>\n<p>Sandara’s calling came one night when a fleet of fishermen, which included her father, was lost in a powerful storm. Sandara prayed to Besmara the Pirate Queen, the goddess of piracy, strife, and sea monsters, and when her father returned the following day, weatherbeaten and half-drowned but still alive, Sandara knew the goddess had answered her prayers. Soon after, Sandara began devoting her time to the worship of Besmara, eventually setting up a small chapel on the Hell Harbor docks dedicated to her.</p>\n<p>Just 3 weeks ago, Sandara’s beloved father died, and she took to the sea, determined to live her life to the hilt, not rot away in some forgotten port. She only made it as far as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}, however, before she fell afoul of Prince Rockface’s press gang and ended up aboard the <em>Storm Reaver</em>. There are worse places to be than a pirate ship, however, and Sandara has taken to her new surroundings like a fish returned to the sea from which it was born. She still bears the raw scars of grief from burying her father, but knows enough to mask that grief on a vessel such as the <em>Storm Reaver</em>. Sandara plans to make the most of her present situation, intending to spread the word of her goddess while expanding her horizons at the same time.</p>\n<p>The night before the adventure starts, Master Scourge made a pass at Sandara, and she responded by slapping the boatswain and making it clear that she finds him repulsive. This event has set up a mutual enmity between the two, while also making her a natural ally of the PCs, should they accept her friendship.</p>\n<h2>Appearance</h2>\n<p>Crowned with a mane of fiery red locks, Sandara looks like someone not to be crossed. Yet the smile lines at the corners of her eyes and the easy way she holds herself hint at a lighter side. She dresses to accentuate her figure, and her whole appearance speaks of the sea, from the seagull feather in her tricorne hat to the sailor tattoos on her arms and the clay pipe thrust into the corner of her mouth.</p>\n<h2>Campaign Role</h2>\n<p>Sandara is designed to give the characters an automatic friend among the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew—in all likelihood, the only one to begin with. How the PCs first meet Sandara is up to you, but two suggestions might work well. The PCs might already know Sandara before the adventure starts, and she is press-ganged at the same time. Alternatively, Sandara can immediately try to befriend the PCs during their first day on the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, regarding them as kindred free spirits who have been brought aboard against their will. Having already had a falling out with Master Scourge, Sandara is concerned about her own skin and believes the PCs might make for helpful allies.</p>\n<p>Sandara hasn’t been aboard the ship long, but she already has a good idea of its layout and has heard the other pirates talking, and can share much of this information with the PCs. Use Sandara as a voice of reason between the PCs and the crew, counseling them to avoid attempting anything too dangerous or attracting the ire of Mr. Plugg or Prince Rockface. She can use her magic to heal injured PCs, and assist them during workdays by adding a +2 bonus on any single check made by a struggling PC, as appropriate.</p>\n<p>As the adventure progresses, Sandara has greater roles to play—first as a prisoner of the grindylows on Bonewrack Isle for the PCs to rescue, and later as an invaluable ally of the PCs when they finally mutiny against Mr. Plugg and Master Scourge at the end of the adventure. She can even become a romantic interest for a PC, if you wish.</p>\n<h3>Too Good To Be True?</h3>\n<p>If met by chance, a character like Sandara might naturally arouse players’ suspicions. Not only is she immediately helpful, but the fact that she returns the PCs’ equipment and happily casts healing spells upon her newfound friends may seem too good to believe. Sandara is free of any sinister motives, however, and is just as she seems.</p>\n<p>Suspicion can be a powerful tool for roleplaying, but be careful not to overdo it and accidentally push the PCs into becoming enemies with Sandara. She is a font of useful knowledge and information, but try not to make her too clever or wise. Sandara likes a drink and a gamble, and these qualities can be used to make her seem vulnerable as well as smart. She can play a significant role throughout the entire Adventure Path as a trusted friend of the PCs, and by starting off well you can quickly make her an important NPC ally.</p>\n<p>It’s extremely unlikely that the PCs make an enemy of Sandara, but if they do, she can become a recurring rival or foe of the PCs. The PCs might very well not be heroes, and their actions may horrify the cleric into joining up with their enemies to oppose them, or might teach her the lesson that no one can ever be trusted, in which case she moves on without them.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"base","_viewcount":4,"role":"Friend of the Players/Swab","location":"The Wormwood","race":"Human","gender":"","age":"","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":{"notes":""},"scrollPos":"{\".description\":50}"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_wu5utkhw5ta","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Crew of the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"E8oHB2WzzqVCFQrE","name":"Campaign Summary","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Campaign Summary</h1>\n<h2>Campaign Summary</h2>\n<p>From here you can expect the following to happen over the course of the campaign arc.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You start the campaign press-ganged onto a Pirate Ship.</li>\n<li>You can expect to find your freedom from Prince Rockface.</li>\n<li>The campaign will be on rails for the first 4-8 sessions while you are a crew member of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>.</li>\n<li>You will have an opportunity to acquire your own ship, through mutiny or other means. </li>\n<li>Once you acquire your own ship, the Lhazaar (and Seas of Eberron) become a large sand box that will be driven by your actions to try and help those that are still alive from Cyre.</li>\n<li>There will be space in the campaign for you to assist Cyrans through piracy and treasure hunting. You can even to attempt to acquire land or a principality for Cyrans. What will you choose?</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Campaign Opening</h2>\n<p>Your journey has taken you to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities}. You all have come here for different reasons. But each of you find yourselves at an inn called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and the Baron}. The night that followed with much drinking, gambling and sea shanties.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Or so you think. You wake in the morning, not remembering much after a certain point. You find yourselves in the hold of a ship out at sea. You are press-ganged, and forced to join the crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, captained by the despicable Mika Rockface. Captain Mika Rockface, infamous as the Prince of the ruthless @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Cloudreaver Principality]{Cloudreaver Principality}. Prince Rockface boldly press gangs you from under the noses of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Seadragon Principality]{Seadragon Principality}.</p>\n</div>\n","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":10},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_sfbrzx24rkb","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Player Character Guide","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"FDTdQ6D3sO3V4tDz","name":"Master Scourge","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Master Scourge is the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> boatswain and master-at-arms, and Mr. Lagraa’s right-hand man. As boatswain, he is in charge of all activities and sailors on deck, and as master-at-arms, he is responsible for discipline. Master Scourge is a sneering man with a braided beard and a mouth full of gold teeth. His body is tall and thin, and even his long coat and heavy boots fail to give any impression of strength or bulk. A sadistic coward, Scourge uses his association with Lagraa as protection and in return has no morals when it comes to the tasks his master sets. He is bold and violent when the odds are stacked in his favor, happily kicking a dying dog in the street if asked to do so. But should that dog get up and bite, he quickly f lees.</p>\n<p>Master Scourge is a key villain in the early part of the adventure, and his whispered words further poison Mr. Lagraa against the PCs. Scourge’s relationship with the PCs is a crucial one. He immediately senses something out of the ordinary about them, and his dreams of rank and fortune soon begin to unravel. Like most bullies, Scourge is a coward at heart, and sets out to discredit and ultimately kill his rivals.</p>\n<p>This enmity is personal, and primarily directed at a single PC, though how this manifests is ultimately up to you. Scourge was recently rejected by Sandara Quinn (see page 56), and any object of her affections is sure to earn his jealousy and hatred. Likewise, Scourge might be jealous of a handsome and talented PC and fear for his own position on the ship. While Scourge focuses his hostility on one PC, he is also happy to intimidate and victimize the other PCs, as well as seeking to discredit the PCs’ friends. He avoids the PCs as a group, however, and immediately goes to Lagraa’s side if threatened. If actually attacked, he also goes to Lagraa, who may have the PCs disciplined.</p>\n<p>Playing the bully requires you to temper the PCs’ anger while ensuring they recognize Scourge as a deadly enemy with far too many allies to simply be killed. Terrified as he is of Prince Rockface and having no desire to be keelhauled, Scourge won’t try to kill the PCs—at least, not at first. Instead, he seeks to poison the other crew members against the PCs, and is likely to succeed with his own small band of admirers, whom the PCs will find hard to convert. In essence, this group becomes a rival adventuring party, but with one crucial difference: these rivals also enjoy the support of Mr. Lagraa. It’s not until events move on to the Man’s Promise in Part Two that Lagraa and Scourge decide to have done with the PCs, but they’ll eventually get their comeuppance at the hands of the PCs in Part Three.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"base","_viewcount":5,"role":"Boatswain and Master-at-Arms","location":"The Wormwood","race":"Half-orc","gender":"","age":"","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":{"notes":"Master Scourge is the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> boatswain and master-at-arms, and Mr. Dabrak’s right-hand man. As boatswain, he is in charge of all activities and sailors on deck, and as master-at-arms, he is responsible for discipline. Master Scourge is a sneering man with a braided beard and a mouth full of gold teeth. His body is tall and thin, and even his long coat and heavy boots fail to give any impression of strength or bulk. A sadistic coward, Scourge uses his association with Dabrak as protection and in return has no morals when it comes to the tasks his master sets. He is bold and violent when