ey’ll eventually get their comeuppance at the hands of the PCs in Part Three."},"scrollPos":"{\".description\":50}"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_wu5utkhw5ta","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Crew of the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"FDc8OuXwl18j9XWe","name":"A Pirate's Day","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">A Pirate's Day</h1>\n<p>The <em>Storm Reaver </em>works on discipline and routine. Prince Rockface's philosophy is that a busy swab is a tired swab, and tired swabs don’t pick fights with each other. After breakfast, the crew work at their allotted jobs until dusk, when they gather on the main deck to witness punishments (the “Bloody Hour”), eat dinner, and receive their rum rations. After punishment time and the evening meal, the crew can do what they wish until dawn bell the next morning. </p>\n<p>Each day, the heroes are assigned tasks to complete, based on the their jobs (cook’s mate, rigger, or swab).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Cook's Mate Tasks]{Cook's Mate Tasks}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Rigging Tasks]{Rigging Tasks}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Swab Tasks]{Swab Tasks}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each task represents a day’s hard work and requires at least one successful skill check to complete. Failing a task’s required skill check results in punishment. The punishment for failing a check is merely a severe verbal reprimand, or at worse, a @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{rope bash}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} results in @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{three lashes}. The number of lashes increases to six if this is the second such failure in a row, to nine lashes for three failures in a row, and so on.</p>\n<p>Work takes place under the watchful eyes of @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Mister Lagraa]{Mr. Lagraa} and @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Master Scourge]{Master Scourge}, and getting away from them is not easy. If a hero refuses to work or is unable to work, she receives a @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{dozen lashes} for the first such offense and a dozen lashes with the cat for the second. A third offense results in the character being put in the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{sweatbox} for 12 hours.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_lasttab":"description","scrollPos":"{\".description\":0}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ptturwq4bg","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"GOOUifvBeOF8x8qZ","name":"Galley","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Galley</h1>\n<p>The galley is the domain of Krornik “Fishguts” Kragshard, the drunken ship’s cook. The cramped and chaotic kitchen holds two wooden worktables, several wooden cupboards, and two small stoves against the port wall, as well as virtually every cooking utensil imaginable and a frightening array of meat cleavers. The kitchen is a madness of dirt, food, and knives, and finding anything in here requires a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check. The stoves are perpetually lit, and large cauldrons bubble away atop them all times. A huge array of spices mingle with barrels of rainwater, two tuns of rum, cupboards full of ship’s biscuit and salted beef, barrels of sauerkraut, and a small supply of fresh vegetables picked up in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}. Despite the chaos, the entire galley functions as a set of masterwork @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Cook's Utensils]{Cook's Utensils} for cooking checks.</p>\n<h3>Valuable Items Lost</h3>\n<p>Several items of value are lost among the ruin and squalor in the galley, each requiring a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check to discover: a masterwork dagger being used as a butcher’s knife, a pair of handaxes used as meat cleavers, 11 knives, a short sword, a vial of holy water, a good lock hanging unused off a pantry cupboard, 2 pounds of soap, four waterskins, a barrel of poor wine, six bottles of good karrnathi brandy worth 20 gp each, three bottles of magnificent rum worth 12 gp each, a large cookbook worth 125 gp (using the tome while cooking grants a +1 bonus on cooking checks), a prosthetic leg made of wood and edged with a silver band worth 45 gp, and 12 sp fallen behind a cupboard. In addition, a trio of harpoons, a spear, and Kroop’s steadfast grapple hang on the walls.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_e26boiu8etj","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"IJ50uKvBPIqcOK84","name":"Cargo Hold","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Cargo Hold</h1>\n<p>This is the ship’s cargo hold. The hold is mostly empty at the start of the adventure, save for the 14 pigs; normally kept caged, they periodically escape and run loose within the hold.</p>\n<p>The ceiling is open to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Weapons Deck]{Weapons Deck} so cargo may be raised and lowered. There is a locked door in the aft wall that leads to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers Quarters]{Officers Quarters}. Towards the bow there are double doors that lead to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Brig]{Brig} as well as a hall passage with ladders up to the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Weapons Deck]{Weapons Deck}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Owlbear Hartshorn]{Owlbear Hartshorn} is invariably chained to the near the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers Quarters]{Officers Quarters} to keep him from causing trouble and to keep people out.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_e26boiu8etj","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"JBrneClXhXYT5ZGX","name":"The Storm Reaver Crew","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">The Storm Reaver Crew</h1>\n<p>Use this chart to track how the characters are influencing other pirates on the <em>Storm Reaver.</em></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"5\">Crew Disposition</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Name</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Role</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Stat</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\">Disposition</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading left\" style=\"width:30%\">Notes</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"bar-heading\" colspan=\"5\"><span class=\"no-class\">Officers</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Mika Rockface}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Captain}</td>\n<td>F dwarf</td>\n<td>Hostile</td>\n<td>Ignores characters</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Mister Lagraa}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{First Mate}</td>\n<td>F orc</td>\n<td>Hostile</td>\n<td>Replaces the human Mr. Plugg; Lagraa is a figure to be hated; suspicious of everyone</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Master Scourge}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Boatswain / Master-at-Arms}</td>\n<td>M half-orc</td>\n<td>Hostile</td>\n<td>Turned into a half-orc from a human; a sadistic coward that uses connect with Mr. Lagraa for power and protection</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Krornik \"Fishguts\" Kragshard}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Cook}</td>\n<td>M dwarf</td>\n<td>Neutral</td>\n<td>Replaces the human Ambrose Kroop</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{\"Cut-Throat\" Grok}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Quartermaster}</td>\n<td>F half-orc</td>\n<td>Neutral</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Grovus Stormbeard}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Sorcerer}</td>\n<td>M dwarf</td>\n<td>Unfriendly</td>\n<td>Replaces peppery Longfarthing; Rockface inner circle</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Riaris Krine}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Master Gunner}</td>\n<td>M orc</td>\n<td>Unfriendly</td>\n<td>Rockface inner circle</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Hakrilli Quarne}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Artificer/Carpenter/Healer}</td>\n<td>F dwarf</td>\n<td>Unfriendly</td>\n<td>Rockface inner circle</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Gragoth}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Gunner's mate}</td>\n<td>M orc</td>\n<td>Hostile</td>\n<td>Replaces Kipper, bootlicker to Lagraa and Scourge</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officers of the Storm Reaver]{Patch \"Salty\" Kolkrinun}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{Boatswain's mate}</td>\n<td>F dwarf</td>\n<td>Hostile</td>\n<td>Replaces Patch Patchsalt, sycophant to Lagraa and Scourge</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[s